-- India's Multi Commodity Exchange shares fall after Kotak Mahindra Bank agrees to buy stake
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Sun Jul 20, 2014 11:45PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, July 21 (Reuters) - Shares in Multi Commodity Exchange of India <MCEI.NS> fell 4.6 percent after private sector lender Kotak Mahindra Bank <KTKM.NS> agreed to buy a 15 percent stake in the company for 4.59 billion rupees ($76.1 million), the bank said in a statement late on Sunday.

Kotak will purchase the stake from bourse operator Financial Technologies (India) Ltd <FITE.NS> and the deal is subject to regulatory approvals, the statement said. [ID:nL6N0PV10K]